    dcterms:language "en" ;
    schema:duration "PT62S"^^xsd:duration ;
    cnt:chars "Simple response times of different layers of control are shown in the graph to the right. Notice the differences in the timeframes for the controllers. This separation in controller timeframes simplifies the control design problem. The individual inverter and plant level control schemes operate at different speeds with the individual unit controls acting faster and plant controller acting slower. In general, the lower layer controls in blue react in microseconds to milliseconds, handling fast electrical dynamics. The higher level plant and system responses shown in red operate in hundreds of milliseconds to seconds, managing broader grid support functions like frequency and voltage control. Inverter control is implemented in an nested loop structure without our controls being slower. Take some time to review the timeframes and then click Next for a discussion on power electronic converters and concepts associated within Verters." ;
    fxs:transcribedBy <https://github.com/SYSTRAN/faster-whisper#tiny.en> ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F5zka3Y5AssZ_44100_48_0.mp3> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/slide/6KhIqryeG83> a fxs:Slide ;
    dcterms:title "Power Electronics Overview" ;
    fxs:identifiedBy "6KhIqryeG83" ;
    fxs:sequenceIndex 5 ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/html5/data/js/6KhIqryeG83.js" ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/res/__5qwmVc81kwm_RES> ;
    schema:identifier "Slide6" ;
    fxs:embedsAsset <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6clJAJkbqLU_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:embedsAsset <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F5h9dgd9t9Du_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:hasNarration <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F6clJAJkbqLU_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:hasNarration <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F5h9dgd9t9Du_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:extractedTextCorpus "AdobeStock_1555366827.jpg; PV arrays generate DC electricity; Power electronics switches; Electric grid requires AC electricity; Power electronics switches \\nVoltage-sourced converter vs current-sourced converter\\nAnalysis of voltage-sourced converter \\nPulse-width modulation; Pulse-width modulation; AdobeStock_1036839997.jpg; Image 22.emf; Rectangle 1; PV arrays generate DC electricity\\nElectric grid requires AC electricity ; Voltage-sourced converter vs current-sourced converter; Analysis of voltage-sourced converter; Power electronic converters synthesize an output voltage based on the grid voltage." .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6clJAJkbqLU_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:Asset ;
    dcterms:format "audio/mpeg" ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/story_content/6clJAJkbqLU_44100_48_0.mp3" ;
    schema:duration "PT41S"^^xsd:duration ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F6clJAJkbqLU_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:NarrationTranscript ;
    dcterms:language "en" ;
    schema:duration "PT41S"^^xsd:duration ;
    cnt:chars "Power electronic converters are used for IBRs such as photovoltaic arrays and wind and best resources. We'll focus on solar photovoltaic resources in this course. A solar panel generates direct current electricity and cannot be directly connected to the alternating current electric grid. Power electronic converters are used to transfer energy between PV arrays and the electric grid. This transfer is accomplished by synthesizing an output voltage based on the requirements of the grid, allowing safe and reliable energy transfer. In this course we'll look at how this voltage is synthesized by a power electronic converter." ;
    fxs:transcribedBy <https://github.com/SYSTRAN/faster-whisper#tiny.en> ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6clJAJkbqLU_44100_48_0.mp3> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F5h9dgd9t9Du_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:Asset ;
    dcterms:format "audio/mpeg" ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/story_content/5h9dgd9t9Du_44100_48_0.mp3" ;
    schema:duration "PT46S"^^xsd:duration ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F5h9dgd9t9Du_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:NarrationTranscript ;
    dcterms:language "en" ;
    schema:duration "PT46S"^^xsd:duration ;
    cnt:chars "Over the next several screens we'll look at 4 power electronic concepts in the context of PV inverters. Power electronic switches are the core components and controlling power flow for my BRs. Within this course when we refer to switches, we are talking about power electronic switches. First, we'll look at how these switches operate. Then, we'll compare voltage source converters with current source converters and discuss why voltage source converters are more common with her newable grid integration applications. We'll examine voltage source converter behavior and how it produces a desired voltage set point. And lastly, we'll look at pulse width modulation or PWM for synthesizing desired output." ;
    fxs:transcribedBy <https://github.com/SYSTRAN/faster-whisper#tiny.en> ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F5h9dgd9t9Du_44100_48_0.mp3> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/slide/5uUiVx1gsqw> a fxs:Slide ;
    dcterms:title "Power Electronic Switches" ;
    fxs:identifiedBy "5uUiVx1gsqw" ;
    fxs:sequenceIndex 6 ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/html5/data/js/5uUiVx1gsqw.js" ;
