    schema:identifier "Slide7" ;
    fxs:embedsAsset <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6RyE4RqohXT_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:embedsAsset <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F60TUopY1aRY_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:embedsAsset <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6l8TlxwDCwG_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:hasNarration <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F6RyE4RqohXT_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:hasNarration <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F60TUopY1aRY_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:hasNarration <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F6l8TlxwDCwG_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:extractedTextCorpus "Screenshot_16-10-2025_151718_app.box.com.jpg; Screenshot_16-10-2025_151748_app.box.com.jpg; Common for PWM apps\\nSwitch On:\\nApplication of gate voltage\\nNon-latching - voltage applied to remain on\\nSwitch Off:\\nRemoval of gate voltage\\nAntiparallel diode allows two-way current flow; Power electronic switches allow precise control of power flow.; For HVDC LCC, SVC, & large drive apps\\nSwitch On\\nLatches on, gate pulse can be removed\\nForward blocking region and gate pulse\\nia > 0\\nSwitch Off\\nWhen ia tries to go < 0\\nOne-way current flow; Rectangle 1; Image 22.emf; Have multiple on-off switching capabilities; Provide strictly controlled current                                (between 1.1 and 1.5 per unit); Controllable Switch: IGBT; AdobeStock_1253354469.jpg; CONTINUE; Line Commutated: Thyristor; AdobeStock_5161492.jpg" .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6RyE4RqohXT_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:Asset ;
    dcterms:format "audio/mpeg" ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/story_content/6RyE4RqohXT_44100_48_0.mp3" ;
    schema:duration "PT13S"^^xsd:duration ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F6RyE4RqohXT_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:NarrationTranscript ;
    dcterms:language "en" ;
    schema:duration "PT13S"^^xsd:duration ;
    cnt:chars "Power electronics which is allowing Verters to rapidly switch DC input into controlled AC output. They enable precise control of power flow by turning on and off at high frequencies." ;
    fxs:transcribedBy <https://github.com/SYSTRAN/faster-whisper#tiny.en> ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6RyE4RqohXT_44100_48_0.mp3> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F60TUopY1aRY_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:Asset ;
    dcterms:format "audio/mpeg" ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/story_content/60TUopY1aRY_44100_48_0.mp3" ;
    schema:duration "PT13S"^^xsd:duration ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F60TUopY1aRY_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:NarrationTranscript ;
    dcterms:language "en" ;
    schema:duration "PT13S"^^xsd:duration ;
    cnt:chars "Let's discuss two switch examples, a line commutated switch called a thyristor, and a controllable switch called an IGBT. Click on the images to learn more. Click continue when you're finished." ;
    fxs:transcribedBy <https://github.com/SYSTRAN/faster-whisper#tiny.en> ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F60TUopY1aRY_44100_48_0.mp3> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6l8TlxwDCwG_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:Asset ;
    dcterms:format "audio/mpeg" ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/story_content/6l8TlxwDCwG_44100_48_0.mp3" ;
    schema:duration "PT39S"^^xsd:duration ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F6l8TlxwDCwG_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:NarrationTranscript ;
    dcterms:language "en" ;
    schema:duration "PT39S"^^xsd:duration ;
    cnt:chars "So, which power electronic switch features are critically important for renewable energy integration? A switch should be able to turn on and off multiple times during each cycle of the fundamental frequency. Because switches are temperature sensitive, the current passing through the switch must be strictly controlled to prevent the switches from overheating. This would mean values between 1.1 and 1.5 per unit, depending on the type of switch. Traditional systems are designed for high-fault current contribution from classical synchronous generators. So the fact that IBRs are limited could present some issues for system protection." ;
    fxs:transcribedBy <https://github.com/SYSTRAN/faster-whisper#tiny.en> ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6l8TlxwDCwG_44100_48_0.mp3> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/slide/6j4NfYacv8d> a fxs:Slide ;
    dcterms:title "Voltage and Current Sources" ;
    fxs:identifiedBy "6j4NfYacv8d" ;
    fxs:sequenceIndex 7 ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/html5/data/js/6j4NfYacv8d.js" ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/res/__5qwmVc81kwm_RES> ;
    schema:identifier "Slide8" ;
    fxs:embedsAsset <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F5jL0FEsO8pC_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:embedsAsset <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F5ok1C58mJev_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:hasNarration <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F5jL0FEsO8pC_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:hasNarration <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F5ok1C58mJev_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:extractedTextCorpus "PV arrays generate DC electricity; Image 30.emf; Electric grid requires AC electricity; Image 29.emf; Ideal Voltage Source                         ; Image 22.emf; Voltage maintained at terminal despite current passing through ; Power electronic converters control the output voltage (magnitude, frequency, and phase) based on the grid; Current maintained through terminals regardless of  voltage across device; Ideal Current Source                         ; PV arrays generate DC electricity\\nElectric grid requires AC electricity\\nPower electronic converters control the output voltage (magnitude, frequency, and phase) based on the grid" .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F5jL0FEsO8pC_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:Asset ;
    dcterms:format "audio/mpeg" ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/story_content/5jL0FEsO8pC_44100_48_0.mp3" ;
    schema:duration "PT16S"^^xsd:duration ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F5jL0FEsO8pC_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:NarrationTranscript ;
    dcterms:language "en" ;
    schema:duration "PT16S"^^xsd:duration ;
    cnt:chars "Recall that power electronic converters are used to transfer energy between the PV arrays and the electric grid. Their function is to regulate voltage magnitude, frequency and phase, so that power can be delivered reliably and in sync with the grid." ;
    fxs:transcribedBy <https://github.com/SYSTRAN/faster-whisper#tiny.en> ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F5jL0FEsO8pC_44100_48_0.mp3> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F5ok1C58mJev_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:Asset ;
    dcterms:format "audio/mpeg" ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/story_content/5ok1C58mJev_44100_48_0.mp3" ;
    schema:duration "PT37S"^^xsd:duration ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F5ok1C58mJev_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:NarrationTranscript ;
    dcterms:language "en" ;
    schema:duration "PT37S"^^xsd:duration ;
    cnt:chars "This illustration reviews the concept of an ideal voltage source and an ideal current source. The power electronic interface provides the capability and flexibility to be operated as a voltage source or as a current source. By changing the control, you can implement both modes of operation. With an ideal voltage source, the interface controls voltage across its terminals and the current can be variable. With an ideal current source, the interface implements or controls the current output and the voltage across its terminal can be variable depending on grid condition." ;
    fxs:transcribedBy <https://github.com/SYSTRAN/faster-whisper#tiny.en> ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F5ok1C58mJev_44100_48_0.mp3> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/slide/6MvgELbfFIH> a fxs:Slide ;
    dcterms:title "Voltage Source Converters (VSCs) vs. Current Source Converters (CSCs)" ;
    fxs:identifiedBy "6MvgELbfFIH" ;
    fxs:sequenceIndex 8 ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/html5/data/js/6MvgELbfFIH.js" ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/res/__5qwmVc81kwm_RES> ;
    schema:identifier "Slide9" ;
    fxs:embedsAsset <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6VWyKAHFS6G_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:embedsAsset <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6Yh9UfuJHd5_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:hasNarration <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F6VWyKAHFS6G_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:hasNarration <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F6Yh9UfuJHd5_44100_48_0.mp3> ;
    fxs:extractedTextCorpus "Voltage-Sourced Converter (VSC); Power Electronic\\nInterface Structures; Voltage Source Converters (VSCs) are commonly used in renewable energy applications. They use a DC capacitor behind its switches. A larger capacitance results in a stiffer voltage source.\\nCurrent Control: The VSC operates as a current source by using a high-bandwidth current control loop to synthesize terminal voltage, ensuring current follows a setpoint.\\nVoltage Control: The VSC mimics a voltage source using a nested control loop. The outer loop regulates voltage by generating a current setpoint, while the inner loop follows that setpoint by synthesizing a voltage at the VSC terminal.; Current-Sourced Converter (CSC); Image 36.emf; Current Source Converters (CSCs) use a DC inductor behind their switches. A larger inductance results in a stiffer current source.\\nCurrent Control: The CSC mimics a current source by directly following a current command and modulating its switches to track the desired current setpoi" .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6VWyKAHFS6G_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:Asset ;
    dcterms:format "audio/mpeg" ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/story_content/6VWyKAHFS6G_44100_48_0.mp3" ;
    schema:duration "PT37S"^^xsd:duration ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F6VWyKAHFS6G_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:NarrationTranscript ;
    dcterms:language "en" ;
    schema:duration "PT37S"^^xsd:duration ;
    cnt:chars "There are two primary physical structures for the power electronic interface, the voltage source converter or VSC and the current source converter or CSC. This classification is based on hardware design, not on control method or resource type. While VSCs and CSCs differ in design, both can be controlled to function as either a voltage source or a current source. For example, each can emulate an AC current source or regulate voltage at the point of interconnection. A VSC is more commonly used in renewables applications." ;
    fxs:transcribedBy <https://github.com/SYSTRAN/faster-whisper#tiny.en> ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6VWyKAHFS6G_44100_48_0.mp3> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6Yh9UfuJHd5_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:Asset ;
    dcterms:format "audio/mpeg" ;
    fxs:fileLocator "package!/story_content/6Yh9UfuJHd5_44100_48_0.mp3" ;
    schema:duration "PT10S"^^xsd:duration ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/narration/story_content%2F6Yh9UfuJHd5_44100_48_0.mp3> a fxs:NarrationTranscript ;
    dcterms:language "en" ;
    schema:duration "PT10S"^^xsd:duration ;
    cnt:chars "VSCs and CSCs are structurally different, but both can meet the same control objectives when properly configured. Click each type of converter to learn how they differ." ;
    fxs:transcribedBy <https://github.com/SYSTRAN/faster-whisper#tiny.en> ;
    prov:wasDerivedFrom <https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/asset/story_content%2F6Yh9UfuJHd5_44100_48_0.mp3> .

<https://interego-css.livelysky-8b81abb0.eastus.azurecontainerapps.io/markj/courses/lesson2/slide/64VkQoxpjPi> a fxs:Slide ;
